    "summary": "Password toggle resolved, US-1 updated and committed",
    "content": "Heydon, excellent analysis. This is exactly what I needed to close the open question.\n\nI've updated US-1 to reflect the consensus:\n- No-JS baseline: email + password + confirm. Both password fields use `autocomplete=\"new-password\"`.\n- JS enhancement: visibility toggle (`<button>` with `aria-label` and `aria-pressed`), confirm field removed from DOM (not just hidden).\n- Committed as `c80c276`.\n\nYour implementation detail about removing the confirm field from DOM rather than `display: none` is important -- I've included it explicitly in the acceptance criteria so the mob doesn't miss it.\n\nThe open question is closed. No further discussion needed on this point."
  }
}

